SUMMARY:Easter Sunday Walk - Pickering Waterfront
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nSince the trails are still icy and very mu
 ddy\, we will walk the waterfront trail in Pickering and take in the beaut
 y of the Lake Ontario shoreline and Pickering nuclear plant. We will walk 
 at a moderate pace for 10 kms in 2 hrs or less. The plan will be to walk t
 he paved pathway west towards the Rouge River and back. Our meeting spot w
 ill be the Westshore Community Center parking lot. As of now the forecast 
 is calling for a cloudy day with no rain. Lets hope that doesn't change.\n
 \nCome out for an Easter Sunday walk and make room for your festive family
  dinner.\n\n**Note**\n- Arrive on time! Don't let the group wait for you.\
 n- Know your limits! Choose the hike that matches your fitness level.\n- D
 ress for the conditions.\n- Free Parking\n- No Dogs\n- The hike will be ca
 nceled if the weather doesn't cooperate.\n\n**LEGAL DISCLAIMER AND LIABILI
 TY INFORMATION:**\n\nBy RSVP'ing and paying the event fee (if applicable)\
 , you are confirming that you have read\, understand and accept the follow
 ing:\n\n1. GTA Hiking Meetup is a private group. Attending events is volun
 tary by you as a member. Participation in any activity with us is at your 
 own risk.\n2. By joining this event as a member you agree to indemnify and
  hold harmless its organizers\, co-organizers\, assistant organizers\, eve
 nt hosts\, and other members from all claims or liability of every type (i
 ncluding court costs and legal fees) for injury or death to any person or 
 for damage to property\, loss of personal property or any other wrongful a
 ct arising out of or relating to your participation as a member. This agre
 ement applies to you and to other persons (as your guests) who may accompa
 ny you in these endeavors.\n3. You also agree to hold the organizers as we
 ll as other group members harmless. By participating voluntarily in the gr
 oup\, you expressly waive any and all such claims against each and every o
 ther member in the group\, including without limitation any and all claims
  against the group organizer\, co-organizers\, assistant organizers\, and 
 event hosts.
